HB 4065
1 growers. An order suspending a license under this subsection is subject to ORS chapter 183. How-
2 ever, the department may not suspend a seed dealer license under this section using the procedure
3 described in ORS 183.430 (2).
4 (4) A seed dealer that fails to make payment on a seed production contract or seed purchase
5 contract as required by a notice given by the department under this section is considered to have
6 authorized the producer or seed grower to sell in a commercially reasonable manner any seed from
7 the contract that is still in the possession of the producer or seed grower. This subsection does not
8 prevent a seed dealer from giving consent to the producer or seed grower by other means and does
9 not supersede the terms of a consent given by other means.
10 (5) The department may charge a producer or seed grower a fee, not to exceed $100 [$50], for
11 determining whether payment has been made in accordance with the terms of a seed production
12 contract or seed purchase contract. The department may charge a producer or seed grower a fee,
13 not to exceed $400 [$200], for notifying a seed dealer in writing regarding the deadline for payment
14 of delinquent amounts plus interest.
15 SECTION 2. ORS 576.802 is amended to read:
16 576.802. (1) If a seed dealer fails to pay a producer for other seed when payment is due under
17 a seed production contract or fails to pay a seed grower for other seed when payment is due under
18 a seed purchase contract, the producer or seed grower may notify the State Department of Agri-
19 culture. Upon notification by a producer or seed grower, the department shall determine whether
20 payment has been made when due. If the department determines that the seed dealer has not made
21 a payment that is due under a seed production contract or seed purchase contract, the department
22 shall notify the seed dealer in writing [that the] of the following requirements:
23 (a) The seed dealer [has 30 days to] must pay the producer or seed grower all delinquent
24 amounts plus interest on each delinquent amount. Interest is calculated at the rate of one percent
25 per month simple interest or the current market interest rate as determined by the depart-
26 ment for loans of an amount similar to the delinquent amount, whichever is higher, from the
27 final payment date for that delinquent amount.
28 (b) The payment required under paragraph (a) of this subsection must occur within 30
29 days of the date that the department’s written notice was issued to the seed dealer.
30 (c) Within the 30-day period specified in paragraph (b) of this subsection, the seed dealer
31 must provide to the department a written notice and supporting documentation verifying
32 that the seed dealer has made the payment required under paragraph (a) of this subsection.
33 (2) A seed production contract or seed purchase contract may not vary the terms of the remedy
34 provided by this section. [A seed dealer may appeal the notice] Notice given by the department under
35 this section [as provided in] is subject to ORS chapter 183. This section does not prevent a producer
36 or seed grower from filing a notice of lien against a seed dealer.
37 (3) If a seed dealer fails to make payment [as required by a notice given by the department under
38 this section] within the 30-day period specified in subsection (1) of this section, the department
39 shall suspend any seed dealer license issued to the dealer until the dealer demonstrates to the sat-
40 isfaction of the department that the dealer is current on all payments due to all producers and seed
41 growers. An order suspending a license under this subsection is subject to ORS chapter 183. How-
42 ever, the department may not suspend a seed dealer license under this section using the procedure
43 described in ORS 183.430 (2).
44 (4) A seed dealer that fails to make payment on a seed production contract or seed purchase
45 contract as required by a notice given by the department under this section is considered to have
